</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Distribution and ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
The new species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="X. J. Zhang, T. Deng, J. T. Chen &amp; H. Sun" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Saxifraga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Saxifraga viridiflora" order="Saxifragales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="viridiflora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Saxifraga viridiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is currently known only from Yongfu County, Guangxi Province, China. It was observed to grow on dry limestone under dense jungles at altitudes between 500 and 600 m.
</paragraph>
